    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "932b642a_631583e4",
        "filename": "tests/libraries/netconf.py",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 574,
      "author": {
        "id": 9422
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-01T08:31:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Based on all i\u0027ve seen/understood: getter.py\u0027s AuthStandalone hardcodes the\nprefix /rests/ and port 8181; then this repo serves RESTCONF at /restconf/ on\n8182 -\u003e so the tool 404s and can\u0027t be used without editing it (also I\u0027m pretty sure it\u0027s unused here). Thiskeeps the same threaded\ndesign (ThreadPoolExecutor of worker_count workers) but reuses\ntemplated_requests, which already targets the right endpoint (we can inline). ~90s for 500 devices. Obviously I am open to making any changes if need be.",
      "parentUuid": "991ee2f4_ea3af06d",
      "revId": "f93b4fdbaf6d27c90cfcc29e10f5bebe8b6a6bee",
      "serverId": "7fc14799-209e-464c-9743-7a06c2c21a81"
    },
